2026-02-20 20:36:41 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "Travel Planner: Create day-by-day itinerary with activities, hotel options (budget/mid/luxury + prices), and budget breakdown (accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total).", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Get\u2011away \u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f50,000 (INR) budget  \n*(All prices are approximate for **February\u202f2026** and shown in Indian Rupees. Prices can vary, so book early to lock in the rates.)*\n\n| Category | What\u2019s Included | Approx. Cost (\u20b9) |\n|----------|----------------|-----------------|\n| **Accommodation** (2 nights) | See three hotel tiers below | \u2013 |\n| **Food & Drinks** | Breakfast (incl. hotel), lunch, dinner, snacks, 2\u202f\u00d7\u202fsoft drinks/juice, 1\u202f\u00d7\u202fcocktail/mocktail | \u20b9\u202f4,000\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| **Local Transport** | Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel & back (taxi/auto), 2\u2011day scooter rental + fuel, occasional auto\u2011rickshaw | \u20b9\u202f2,500\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| **Attractions & Activities** | Beach entry (free), entry fees for forts, museums, water\u2011sport voucher, sunset cruise | \u20b9\u202f3,500\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f5,500 |\n| **Miscellaneous** | Souvenirs, tips, Wi\u2011Fi, emergency buffer | \u20b9\u202f1,000\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f1,500 |\n| **Total (approx.)** | \u2013 | **\u20b9\u202f45,000\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f50,000** |\n\n> **Bottom line:** Even the \u201cluxury\u201d option stays comfortably under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202fk ceiling, leaving a small buffer for extra shopping or a spa treatment.\n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Hotel Options (2\u202fnights)\n\n| Tier | Hotel (Area) | Room Type | Approx. Rate per Night (incl. taxes & breakfast) | Total for 2 Nights | Highlights |\n|------|--------------|-----------|---------------------------------------------------|---------------------|------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Guesthouse** (Calangute) | Standard Double | **\u20b9\u202f2,200** | \u20b9\u202f4,400 | Clean rooms, rooftop garden, walking distance to Calangute Beach. |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim) | Deluxe Double with sea view | **\u20b9\u202f4,800** | \u20b9\u202f9,600 | Pool, free Wi\u2011Fi, close to Candolim & Baga beaches, good restaurant on\u2011site. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim) | Ocean\u2011front Deluxe | **\u20b9\u202f12,500** | \u20b9\u202f25,000 | 5\u2011star service, private beach, multiple dining venues, spa & fitness centre. |\n\n*All three hotels include a complimentary breakfast. If you prefer a boutique vibe, **The Park Baga** (mid\u2011range) is another good pick at ~\u20b9\u202f5,200/night.*\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Transport Details\n\n| Segment | Mode | Approx. Cost |\n|---------|------|--------------|\n| **Airport \u2192 Hotel** (arrival) | Pre\u2011booked taxi/auto (\u2248\u202f10\u202fkm) | \u20b9\u202f800\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f1,200 |\n| **Hotel \u2192 Airport** (departure) | Same as above | \u20b9\u202f800\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f1,200 |\n| **Getting around** | **Scooter rental** (150\u202fkm/day limit) + fuel | \u20b9\u202f350\u202f/\u202fday + \u20b9\u202f150 fuel \u2248 **\u20b9\u202f1,000** total |\n| **Occasional auto\u2011rickshaw** (short hops) | Pay\u2011per\u2011ride | \u20b9\u202f200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f300 |\n\n*If you prefer not to ride a scooter, a day\u2011pass for **Goa Smart Bus** (\u20b9\u202f300) plus occasional auto\u2011rickshaws will keep you under \u20b9\u202f2,500 total.*\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Day\u2011by\u2011Day Itinerary  \n\n### **Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival, North Goa Highlights**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details / Cost |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **08:00** | Arrive at Dabolim Airport | Taxi to hotel (\u20b9\u202f1,000) |\n| **09:30** | Check\u2011in, freshen up | \u2013 |\n| **10:30** | **Calangute Beach** \u2013 stroll, water\u2011sport intro (parasailing) | Parasailing voucher: **\u20b9\u202f1,200** |\n| **12:30** | Lunch at **Fisherman\u2019s Wharf** (Calangute) \u2013 Goan fish thali | **\u20b9\u202f800** |\n| **14:00** | **Fort Aguada** & **Sinquerim Beach** \u2013 historic fort, lighthouse, sea\u2011view photo ops | Entry free, parking **\u20b9\u202f50** |\n| **16:30** | **Baga Beach** \u2013 relax, shop the market stalls | Snacks & drinks **\u20b9\u202f300** |\n| **18:30** | Sunset at **Anjuna Beach** \u2013 watch the famous sunset, optional beach shack dinner | Dinner at **Curlies** \u2013 **\u20b9\u202f1,200** |\n| **20:30** | Return to hotel, night\u2011cap at hotel bar (optional) | Cocktail **\u20b9\u202f500** |\n| **22:00** | Rest / optional early\u2011night walk on the beach | \u2013 |\n\n**Total Day\u202f1 spend (incl. meals, activities, transport):** ~\u20b9\u202f5,200  \n\n---\n\n### **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa & Chill**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details / Cost |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **07:30** | Breakfast at hotel (included) | \u2013 |\n| **08:30** | **Old Goa Churches** \u2013 Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus & Se\u202fCathedral (UNESCO sites) | Entry free, donation **\u20b9\u202f50** |\n| **10:30** | **Sahakari Spice Farm** \u2013 guided tour, spice tasting, lunch | **\u20b9\u202f1,200** (incl. lunch) |\n| **13:00** | Head to **Colva Beach** \u2013 relax, optional water\u2011sport (jet\u2011ski) | Jet\u2011ski **\u20b9\u202f1,500** (30\u202fmin) |\n| **15:30** | **Shri Mangueshi Temple** (cultural stop) | Free, modest donation **\u20b9\u202f30** |\n| **17:00** | **Sunset Cruise** on the Mandovi River (live music, snacks) | **\u20b9\u202f1,800** per person |\n| **19:30** | Dinner at **Martin\u2019s Corner** (Betal\u202fVaddo) \u2013 famous Goan crab & pork | **\u20b9\u202f1,200** |\n| **21:30** | Return to hotel, pack, enjoy a night\u2011cap or a walk on the beach | \u2013 |\n| **23:00** | Check\u2011out (if you have a late flight, store luggage at hotel & head to airport) | \u2013 |\n| **23:45** | Taxi to Dabolim Airport | \u20b9\u202f1,000 |\n\n**Total Day\u202f2 spend (incl. meals, activities, transport):** ~\u20b9\u202f6,200  \n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 Full Budget Breakdown (example using **mid\u2011range** hotel)\n\n| Item | Cost (\u20b9) |\n|------|----------|\n| **Accommodation** (The Flora Residency) | 9,600 |\n| **Food & Drinks** (Day\u202f1\u202f+\u202fDay\u202f2) | 6,000 |\n| **Local Transport** (airport taxis + scooter + fuel) | 2,500 |\n| **Attractions & Activities** (parasailing, spice\u2011farm, jet\u2011ski, cruise, entry fees) | 5,500 |\n| **Miscellaneous / Souvenirs** | 1,200 |\n| **Grand Total** | **\u20b9\u202f24,800** |\n\n> **Why the total is far below \u20b9\u202f50\u202fk?**  \n> - The mid\u2011range hotel is the most expensive line\u2011item.  \n> - All other categories are deliberately kept modest but still give you a full Goan experience.  \n> - The remaining **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f25,000** can be used for:  \n>   - Up\u2011grading to a **luxury** stay (adds ~\u20b9\u202f15,400).  \n>   - Adding a **spa treatment** (\u20b9\u202f2,500\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f4,000).  \n>   - More **shopping** at Anjuna flea market or local art galleries.  \n>   - Extending the trip by a night (budget\u2011hotel ~\u20b9\u202f2,200).  \n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 Quick Tips & Hacks\n\n| Tip | How it Saves Money / Improves Experience |\n|-----|-------------------------------------------|\n| **Book scooter & hotel together** on platforms like **Goibibo** or **MakeMyTrip** \u2013 you often get a 5\u201110\u202f% bundle discount. |\n| **Eat where locals eat** \u2013 beach shacks (e.g., **Mum\u2019s Kitchen**, **Susegado**) serve authentic Goan fare for \u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f500 per plate. |\n| **Carry a reusable water bottle** \u2013 refill at hotels or beach kiosks (\u20b9\u202f20 for a large bottle). |\n| **Cash is king** for small vendors & auto\u2011rickshaws; keep \u20b9\u202f2,000\u2011\u20b9\u202f3,000 in small denominations. |\n| **Sun protection** \u2013 sunscreen (\u20b9\u202f250) and a hat will keep you comfortable for long beach hours. |\n| **Travel insurance** \u2013 a basic 2\u2011day policy costs ~\u20b9\u202f300 and gives peace of mind. |\n\n---\n\n## 6\ufe0f\u20e3 Sample Packing List (2\u202fdays)\n\n| Item | Qty |\n|------|-----|\n| Light cotton shirts / tank tops | 2\u20113 |\n| Shorts / comfortable trousers | 2 |\n| Swimsuit / boardshorts | 1\u20112 |\n| Flip\u2011flops + comfortable sandals | 1 each |\n| Sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+) | 1 |\n| Sunglasses & hat | 1 each |\n| Small day\u2011backpack | 1 |\n| Portable charger / power bank | 1 |\n| Basic first\u2011aid (plasters, pain\u2011relief) | \u2013 |\n| Reusable water bottle | 1 |\n\n---\n\n### \ud83c\udf89 Ready to book?\n\n1. **Reserve your hotel** (choose budget/mid/luxury).  \n2. **Pre\u2011book the airport taxi** via **Ola/ Uber** or a local operator.  \n3. **Rent the scooter** online (e.g., **Royal Brothers**, **Goa Bike Rentals**) \u2013 they\u2019ll deliver it to your hotel.  \n4. **Buy activity vouchers** (parasailing, spice\u2011farm, cruise) a day before arrival to lock in prices.  \n\nEnjoy the sun, sea, and spice\u2011laden vibes of Goa! If you need any tweaks\u2014like a different activity mix, a vegetarian\u2011friendly food plan, or a 3\u2011day extension\u2014just let me know. \ud83c\udf34\u2708\ufe0f"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py] line number [13] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-87e319fe-c404-4800-bf32-f3f9a649fd14", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "## What the error means\n\n```\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\nThe traceback tells us that somewhere in **`GoogleMap.py`** (line\u202f13) you are raising (or creating) an instance of a custom exception called **`HolidayAgentException`**, but the constructor (`__init__`) of that class expects **two** arguments:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_message, error_detail):\n        super().__init__(error_message)\n        self.detail = error_detail\n```\n\nWhen you call it like:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API failed\")\n```\n\nonly the first argument (`error_message`) is supplied, so Python complains that the required second argument (`error_detail`) is missing.\n\n---\n\n## Quick fixes (choose one that fits your design)\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Make `error_detail` optional (most common)\n\nIf you don\u2019t always have extra detail, give the parameter a default value:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        super().__init__(error_message)\n        self.detail = error_detail\n```\n\nNow you can raise it with **one** or **two** arguments:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API failed\")               # detail = \"\"\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API failed\", \"Timeout\")   # detail = \"Timeout\"\n```\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Always pass a second argument\n\nIf you want the exception to always carry extra context, modify the raise site (line\u202f13) to include a detail string:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    \"Google Maps API failed\",\n    f\"Status code {response.status_code}, response: {response.text}\"\n)\n```\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Use a more Pythonic built\u2011in exception\n\nIf you don\u2019t need a custom class, you could simply raise a built\u2011in exception with a rich message:\n\n```python\nraise RuntimeError(\n    f\"Google Maps API failed \u2013 status {response.status_code}: {response.text}\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step\u2011by\u2011step debugging guide\n\n1. **Open `GoogleMap.py`** and locate line\u202f13 (the line that raises the exception).  \n2. **Check the definition** of `HolidayAgentException` (usually near the top of the file or in a shared `exceptions.py`).  \n3. **Decide** whether you want the second argument to be mandatory or optional.  \n4. **Apply one of the fixes** above.  \n5. **Run the script again** (or run the specific function that calls the Google Maps API) to verify the error is gone.  \n\n---\n\n## Example \u2013 Full corrected snippet\n\nBelow is a minimal, self\u2011contained version of what the file might look like after applying the most flexible fix (making `error_detail` optional).\n\n```python\n# GoogleMap.py\nimport requests\n\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent project.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, error_message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        super().__init__(error_message)\n        self.detail = error_detail\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        # Show both parts when the exception is printed\n        base = super().__str__()\n        return f\"{base} | Detail: {self.detail}\" if self.detail else base\n\n\ndef get_place_coordinates(place_name: str, api_key: str):\n    \"\"\"\n    Calls the Google Maps Geocoding API and returns (lat, lng).\n    Raises HolidayAgentException on any failure.\n    \"\"\"\n    endpoint = \"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json\"\n    params = {\"address\": place_name, \"key\": api_key}\n    try:\n        response = requests.get(endpoint, params=params, timeout=10)\n        response.raise_for_status()          # raises HTTPError for 4xx/5xx\n        data = response.json()\n\n        if data.get(\"status\") != \"OK\":\n            raise HolidayAgentException(\n                \"Google Maps API returned non\u2011OK status\",\n                f\"status={data.get('status')}, error_message={data.get('error_message')}\"\n            )\n\n        location = data[\"results\"][0][\"geometry\"][\"location\"]\n        return location[\"lat\"], location[\"lng\"]\n\n    except requests.RequestException as exc:\n        # Network\u2011level problems (timeout, DNS, connection error, etc.)\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\n            \"Failed to reach Google Maps API\",\n            str(exc)\n        ) from exc\n\n\n# ----------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Example usage (remove or guard with if __name__ == \"__main__\" in prod)\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    API_KEY = \"YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY\"\n    try:\n        lat, lng = get_place_coordinates(\"Baga Beach, Goa, India\", API_KEY)\n        print(f\"Baga Beach \u2192 lat: {lat}, lng: {lng}\")\n    except HolidayAgentException as e:\n        print(f\"\u274c Error: {e}\")\n```\n\n**What changed?**\n\n| Change | Reason |\n|--------|--------|\n| `error_detail: str = \"\"` in `__init__` | Makes the second argument optional, preventing the \u201cmissing argument\u201d error when you only pass a message. |\n| `__str__` override | Gives a nice printable representation that includes the detail when it exists. |\n| Wrapped the request in a `try/except` and re\u2011raised a `HolidayAgentException` with both a message **and** the original exception text. | Provides richer debugging info without breaking the flow. |\n\n---\n\n## How to test the fix quickly\n\n```bash\npython - <<'PY'\nfrom GoogleMap import get_place_coordinates, HolidayAgentException\n\ntry:\n    # Intentionally use a bad API key to trigger the exception path\n    get_place_coordinates(\"Calangute Beach, Goa\", api_key=\"INVALID_KEY\")\nexcept HolidayAgentException as e:\n    print(\"Caught custom exception:\")\n    print(e)               # Should show both message and detail\nPY\n```\n\nYou should see something like:\n\n```\nCaught custom exception:\nGoogle Maps API returned non\u2011OK status | Detail: status=REQUEST_DENIED, error_message=The provided API key is invalid.\n```\n\nIf you get that output, the exception class works as intended and the original \u201cmissing argument\u201d error is resolved.\n\n---\n\n## Next steps for your project\n\n1. **Search for other places** where `HolidayAgentException` is raised and verify they now pass the correct number of arguments (or rely on the default).  \n2. **Add unit tests** for the exception handling path so future refactors will surface similar mismatches early.  \n3. **Consider logging** the `error_detail` to a file or monitoring system (e.g., using Python\u2019s `logging` module) instead of only printing it.  \n\n---\n\n### TL;DR\n\n*Your custom exception expects two arguments, but you only gave one.*  \n**Fix:** either make the second argument optional (`error_detail: str = \"\"`) **or** always supply a second argument when raising the exception. The example above shows a clean, production\u2011ready implementation.  \n\nIf you run into any other traceback lines or need help wiring this into the larger HolidayAgent workflow, just drop the next error message here and we\u2019ll keep debugging together! \ud83d\ude80", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "The user reports an error in a python script. As ChatGPT, we need to respond helpfully, maybe explain the error, suggest fix. Provide debugging steps. No code execution needed. Provide explanation of missing argument in exception init. Suggest adding default or passing argument. Also maybe show corrected class definition. Provide steps."}}], "created": 1771600005, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_e10890e4b9", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 1611, "prompt_tokens": 2538, "total_